# Chrome Extension — Cognitive State Detection

A hackathon Chrome extension that passively monitors user behavioral signals (keyboard, mouse, scroll, tab activity, page content, environment) and syncs snapshots every 30 seconds to a backend API. Only the **onboarding** uses a side panel; all runtime UI uses a **floating popup** in the bottom-right corner.

---

## Architecture Overview

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                   Chrome Extension                   │
│                                                     │
│  ┌──────────────┐   ┌───────────────────────────┐  │
│  │ manifest.json│   │  background.js (SW)        │  │
│  └──────────────┘   │  - State aggregation        │  │
│                     │  - Tab/idle/env tracking    │  │
│  ┌──────────────┐   │  - 30s sync timer           │  │
│  │ sidepanel/   │   │  - Pending snapshot buffer  │  │
│  │ onboarding   │   └───────────┬───────────────┘  │
│  └──────────────┘               │ message bus       │
│                                 │                   │
│  ┌──────────────┐   ┌───────────▼───────────────┐  │
│  │ popup/       │   │  content.js (injected)     │  │
│  │ floating HUD │◄──│  - Keyboard stream         │  │
│  └──────────────┘   │  - Mouse stream             │  │
│                     │  - Scroll stream            │  │
│                     │  - Page content stream      │  │
│                     └───────────────────────────┘  │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
         │
         │ POST /api/snapshot (every 30s)
         ▼
   Backend API (localhost:8000)
```

---

